From: Deckanator <https://github.com/sedyh/deckanator>
Subject: [PATCH] disable HID backend to avoid use-after-free on Steam Deck

The libmanette HID backend (added in 0.2.11) installs a GLib polling
GSource that captures a raw `self` pointer and talks to hidraw every
4 ms. When Steam Input rapidly hot-plugs the Steam Deck's virtual
controller (which happens on action-set switches, e.g. Desktop <-> Gamepad),
the backend GObject is disposed while a queued timer callback is still
in flight, producing a use-after-free that trips
`MANETTE_IS_BACKEND (self)` inside `manette_backend_emit_event` as
called from WebKitGTK's gamepad provider. This crashes the whole
WebKitWebProcess on the first input.

We don't need the HID driver for Deckanator: Steam Input always exposes
the Steam Deck gamepad as a virtual XInput device (28DE:11FF) on evdev,
which libmanette handles via the stable evdev backend. Every other
gamepad already used the evdev path before 0.2.11.

Disable the HID backend early in `initialize` so the hid path is never
taken, no timer is ever scheduled, and `manette_backend_emit_event`
only ever sees evdev backends. Other gamepad support is unaffected.
---
 src/manette-hid-backend.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/manette-hid-backend.c b/src/manette-hid-backend.c
--- a/src/manette-hid-backend.c
+++ b/src/manette-hid-backend.c
@@ -93,6 +93,8 @@ manette_hid_backend_initialize (ManetteBackend *backend)
   ManetteHidBackend *self = MANETTE_HID_BACKEND (backend);
   const struct hid_device_info *info;
   g_autoptr (GError) error = NULL;
   guint poll_rate;
 
+  return FALSE;
+
   self->hid = hid_open_path (self->filename);
   if (!self->hid) {
     g_debug ("Failed to open hid device: %ls", hid_error (NULL));
